Description: Store user configuration in $HOME/.config/caprice32/cap32.cfg
 On first launch, copy the system default /etc/cap32.cfg into
 $HOME/.config/caprice32/cap32.cfg (creating the directory as needed).
 Subsequent launches read from and write to that user file, following
 the XDG Base Directory convention.  The system file in /etc is never
 modified.
 .
 The command-line --config option still overrides this path.
 Portable / development fallbacks (executable directory, XDG_CONFIG_HOME,
 /etc, macOS bundle) are kept for non-installed use.
Author: Nicolas HOUDELOT <nicolas@demosdebs.org>
